 We have to switch on: Vaughan 

 - FIRST TEST 

 Hasan Raza set to make comeback 

 Shoaib Akhtar during training in Multan on Friday. (AFP) 

Multan: England captain and opener Marcus Trescothick feels England have prepared well for the first Test with Pakistan starting on Saturday despite the loss of Michael Vaughan and defeat in the Lahore tour match. But he said on Friday: We have to switch on for the Test. We have to be mentally up to it and we have to adapt ourselves to the different challenges thrown at us in the series. 

Inzamam highlighted leg-spinner Danish Kaneria as their key player. Shoaib Akhtar returns after last playing for Pakistan in January before being recalled from Australia due to fitness problems. 

 Meanwhile, Hasan Raza, Pakistans youngest to play a Test, is set to make a comeback to international cricket on Saturday. 

Teams 

Pakistan (from): Inzamam-ul Haq (captain), Younis Khan, Salman Butt, Shoaib Malik, Mohammed Yousuf, Asim Kamal, Shahid Afridi, Hasan Raza, Kamran Akmal, Shoaib Akhtar, Rana Naved-ul-Hasan, Mohammed Sami, Shabbir Ahmed, Mushtaq Ahmed, Arshad Khan and Danish Kaneria. 

England (from): Marcus Trescothick (captain), Andrew Strauss, Ian Bell, Andrew Flintoff, Kevin Pietersen, Paul Collingwood, Geraint Jones, Ashley Giles, Shaun Udal, Steve Harmison, Matthew Hoggard, James Anderson, Matthew Prior, Liam Plunkett and Alex Loudon. 

Umpires: Simon Taufel, Billy Bowden. TV: Asad Rauf. Match Referee: Roshan Mahanama. (Agencies) 




